Package: ettbc
Title: Emulating a Target Trial for Breast Cancer Screening
Version: 0.0.0.9025
Authors@R: c(
    person(
      given = "Douglas Ezra",
      family = "Morrison",
      email = "demorrison@ucdavis.edu",
      role = c("aut", "cre"),
      comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-7195-830X")
    )
  )
Description: Implements the clone-censor step of the target trial emulation
    methodology for studying the effect of sustained screening mammography on
    breast cancer mortality, following the approach of García-Albéniz et al.
    (2020) <doi:10.7326/M18-1199>. Provides functions to clone participants
    into two trial arms (STOPBASE and CONTINUE), apply per-arm censoring rules,
    expand the resulting dataset to a long format suitable for
    inverse-probability-weighted survival analysis, compute IPW weights,
    estimate marginal survival curves via g-computation, and extract mammogram
    events from Medicare claims data.
